            "id": "47e27e448a394e8d84881",
            "questionText": "A newly discovered celestial object has a surface temperature of $!$20,000^{\\circ}\\text{C}$!$. Convert this temperature to Kelvin.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "b833b79e4ef342e79b404",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct conversion formula for transforming a temperature from $!$^{\\circ}C$!$ to Kelvin. Choose the formula that correctly expresses this conversion.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f4f99f5b-01f4-45fa-b6a7-34af17a4fa55"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$K = C + 273.15$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$K = C - 273.15$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$K = C \\times 273.15$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "04d3218c0293401bb0b86",
                    "stepText": "Now that we've selected the appropriate conversion formula, apply it by adding $!$273.15$!$ to the given temperature in Celsius ($!$20,000^{\\circ}C$!$) to convert it to Kelvin. Compute the resulting value and round it if necessary.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "20273"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "K",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f4f99f5b-01f4-45fa-b6a7-34af17a4fa55"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
