            "questionText": "A research team observes a distant galaxy with a recession speed of $!$49000\\ \\text{ km/s}$!$ at a distance of $!$7 \\times 10^8\\ \\text{ light-years}$!$. Given that $!$1\\ \\text{ light-year } = 9.5 \\times 10^{12}\\ \\text{ km}$!$, $!$1\\ \\text{ Mpc} = 3.086 \\times 10^{19}\\ \\text{ km}$!$, and $!$1\\ \\text{ year} = 3.1536 \\times 10^7\\ \\text{ seconds}$!$, calculate the age of the Universe in $!$\\text{years}$!$ using the Hubble constant in $!$\\text{km/s/Mpc}$!$ derived from these observations.",
